https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Daredevil: Season One (2012) #1
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Meet Matt Murdock, One Of New York's Finest Attorneys By Day And Swashbuckling Crime-Fighter Daredevil By Night! Discover The Dark Secrets Behind His First Days In The Costume, As The Man Without Sight Became The Man Without Fear-And One Of The Greatest Heroes In Comic History. Daredevil Faces Off Against The Owl, Purple Man And Mr. Fear For The First Time...But It's Not What You Remember!

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Nova (2013) #5
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description:
The origin of the most talked about new character of the year comes to a shattering conclusion.
Jeph Loeb and Ed McGuinness, two of the most popular creators in comics, bring you an Infinite-ly dramatic turning point in the life of Nova as he discovers that something out in the galaxy is threatening everything he knows.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Nova (2013) #4
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: The mysteries surrounding the disappearance of Sams dad deepen and the helmet leads Nova into intergalactic conflict that will affect the entire Marvel Universe!

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Nova (2013) #3
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Its time for Sam Alexanders Training Day. And with the Guardians of Galaxy s Gamora and Rocket Raccoon in charge, Nova soon learns that old lesson Practice Makes Painful!

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Nova (2013) #2
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description:
A boy, a helmet, and an intergalactic legacy!
Sam Alexander isnt just any 15-year old, hes just been recruited to the Nova Corps: the Universes police force.
What do you get when you pair a raccoon, a green alien lady and a scared teenager? An amazingly awesome origin tale!

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Nova (2013) #1
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: The Human Rocket returns! Youve followed him through the history making (and changing!) AvX and now the mystery of the all-new Nova are revealed in this breathtaking new ongoing by the best-selling, award winning team of Jeph Loeb and Ed McGuinness (RED HULK, Avengers X-Sanction). Sam Alexander is a kid bound by the gravity of a small town and a father whose ridiculous, drunken fairy tales about a Nova Corps were just another heavy burden in a life full of them. But luckily for Sam Alexandersoon gravity wont even matter. And those troubles? Its like theyre a billion miles away.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Uncanny Avengers (2012) #9
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Ragnark Now continues! A team divided. The Apocalypse Twins triumphant.  Wolverine discovers The Midnight City and soon wishes he hadnt. The Horsemen of Death shatter the Avengers body and soul!

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Uncanny Avengers (2012) #8
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Xavier is dead, now begins the age of The Apocalypse Twins! Now begins Ragnark and it's all Thor's fault! S.W.O.R.D. Peak station is attacked by Apocalypse's Ship! A Celestial's fate so shocking, so impossible, it will rock the Marvel Universe to its core.This is it, Ragnark is now and not even the Uncanny Avengers can hold it back!

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Uncanny Avengers (2012) #7
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Enter The Apocalypse Twins! The beginning of the end begins with their arrival! Why do they seek to anger The Celestials? What is their connection to Kang? How is Thor responsible for their mighty power?! A death at the hands of an Avenger divides the team! Will Sunfire torture an S-Man to save mutant lives?

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Uncanny Avengers (2012) #6
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: The Apocalypse Twins Part 1.  Thor vs Apocalypse in the 11th Century! The Avengers ancestors are being hunted and only a young Thor can save them!  And with Rama Tut and Kang pulling the strings, you know nothing good can come from any of it.  The future begins here and the effects will reverberate across the Marvel Universe for years to come!

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Uncanny Avengers (2012) #5
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Wonder Man, Wasp and Sunfire join the team just in time for Grim Reapers revenge!  Tension between the team builds as Havoks leadership is questioned!  Witness the death of a major character at the hands of an Avenger in broad daylight!

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Uncanny Avengers (2012) #4
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description:
Red Skull and his S-Men move forward their take over of New York.
A member of the Uncanny Avengers joins the S-Men!
When the chips are down, the fight all but lost, one Avenger must rise and face the terrible might of The Omega Skull!

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Uncanny Avengers (2012) #3
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Red Skull is using his new powers to incite violence against mutants across the globe! Scarlet Witch and Rogue make a terrible discovery that will haunt them forever! The Uncanny Avengers feel the full might of Red Skull's S-Men!

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Uncanny Avengers (2012) #2
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Marvel Now! continues with Cap's newest Avengers! What are Red Skull's new powers? Havok and Thor vs. Honest John, The Living Propaganda! Rogue and Scarlet Witch vs. Red Skull's S-Men! Wolverine and Cap find the truth behind worldwide mutant murder!

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Uncanny Avengers (2012) #1
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: THIS IS IT! The greatest era of the Marvel Universe starts here! From the ashes of AvX an all-new, all-different Avengers assemble! - Captain America begins his quest to create a sanctioned Avengers unit comprised of Avengers and X-Men, humans and mutants working together - so why is Professor Xavier's dream more at risk than ever? - The first attack of the most loathsome villain in history will quake the Marvel Universe forever! - The funeral of one of Marvel's greatest heroes!

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Astonishing X-Men (2004) #58
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Warbird is on the run, labeled an enemy of Earth as well as of the Shiar!The X-Men must choose whether to help her or bring her in.Whats the secret of the alien artifact shes uncovered?

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Astonishing X-Men (2004) #59
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Back from their honeymoon, Northstar and Kyle face a threat at homewhile Northstar faces another threat all on his own!And deep in space, something is coming that might literally tear the team apart!

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Astonishing X-Men (2004) #60
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Part 2 of X-TERMINATION! With Nightcrawler wreaking havoc on the very fabric of reality, Wolverine calls in his street team. Confronted with the doppelganger of their dead friend, will the team be able to do whats necessary to stop him?

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Astonishing X-Men (2004) #61
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: X-TERMINATION Part 5 AOA and our Earth are on the verge of destruction! Plus, a final goodbye between Wolverine and AOA Jean Grey!

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Astonishing X-Men (2004) #62
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Iceman is changed after his multi-dimensional ordeal. What aftershocks will this have in his life?  And what is left of the Astonishing X-Men, The X-Treme X-Men and the Age of Apocalypse?

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Astonishing X-Men (2004) #63
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Over the course of his life, Bobby Drake, a.k.a. Iceman, has taken on and beaten the worst enemies the world -- and the universe -- can throw at him. But is the most dangerous villain yet to come? And could it be none other than...Bobby himself?

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Astonishing X-Men (2004) #64
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: A catastrophic storm has buried much of the northern hemisphere under the deadly weight of snow, creating a kingdom where only one man rules: Bobby Drake.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Astonishing X-Men (2004) #65
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: As the world shivers beneath a heavy blanket of snow, it's time for the final showdown. When all is said and done, who is Bobby Drake? What kind of man will he be? And how can he reconcile the things that he's done?

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Astonishing X-Men (2004) #66
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: In the aftermath of Iceman's assault on the world, the X-Men need some time to reflect and take stock of their relationships. What will come from this? And will it send one character down a new path away from the X-Men?

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Astonishing X-Men (2004) #67
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Wolverine and Gambit, on the road, in a stolen Lamborghiniwith an alien stuffed in the teeny tiny trunk, and more aliens tailing them. What could possibly go wrong?

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Astonishing X-Men (2004) #68
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Through thick and thin, from marriage to apocalypse, the X-Men have always stood together as a family. Is there anything in this world that could break them up?
